section.p:
You can see the xmin, xmax, cmin, and
          cmax columns for any row with a SELECT
        statement:SELECT xmin, xmax, cmin, cmax, * FROM tablename;

The SQL SET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL statement sets the isolation mode
        for the current transaction. The mode must be set before any SELECT,
          INSERT, DELETE, UPDATE, or
          COPY
        statements:BEGIN;
SET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL SERIALIZABLE;
...
COMMIT;
